node.text:
—Long overdue for not only another ASB Filmz production but really a collaboration with some of our closest pals that are fellow locals and neighbors in Seaside, California. We're talking about @otherbrotherbeer! These folks opened last October, after years of planning and community outreach. Their presence is critical in the progression of our local beer culture, and they've been releasing some incredible suds! For this collaboration we focused on creating a fermentation profile that was neutral, highlighting fresh Nelson Sauvin, Galaxy & New Zealand Cascade (also called Taiheke) from the 2020 crop year. One whiff & sip will not leave you guessing the hop profile in this one, it's definitively Southern Hemisphere all the way: ripe mango, passion fruit, guava and lil' bit of the diesel dank! Don't sleep on this beer, plenty of 4-packs await on burphopsnow.com for shipping, and we've got a bunch at all three locations. Even grab a pint on draft outside at @heermannslanding at Other Brother Beer!
...
As for the video production, we should state that it has absolutely nothing to do with the pun on the iconic 1987 film upon which the beer is based on. Just some good old fashioned competitive goofiness, reflecting what an actual collaboration at our brewery is still like, Covid or not!!

node.text:
NELSON, BABY! With a Thiol Turbo Boost!⚡️💥⚡️
...
One of our favorite hops, with some exciting new developments to coax out the thiols and tropical flavors! We take 100% Nelson Sauvin hops from @freestylehops in New Zealand and apply it to our Hazy IPA base. Combine that with @phantasm.nz freeze dried sauvignon blanc grape skins and a bioengineered expressive yeast from @berkeley_yeast which results in the TTB....aka Thiol Turbo Boost! Thiols are tiny compounds with a big impact on aroma and flavor, attributing much of tropical notes you find in fruit, wine & now, beer! This process simply squeezes out as many thiols as possible through fermentation with the right mix of "precursors" saturated in the wort.
...
Grab it online at asb.beer for shipping throughout California, and at all three locations this weekend! Happy Saturday folks.

LASER PHOCUS! 📱👁👁🕹Available for shipping throughout California at asb.beer, and at all locations this weekend! About the beer:
...
Introducing a new twist to our Hazy IPAs: the Thiol Turbo Boost™ (TTB). Laser Phocus is the first beer with this treatment, which is essentially the confluence of two new elements, among a few other proprietary techniques. It starts with a product called Phantasm (@phantasm.nz): freeze dried Sauvignon Blanc grape skins from New Zealand that are loaded with Thiol precursors. Then we utilize a bioengineered yeast strain from @berkeley_yeast which takes Thiol precursors and transforms them into thiol compounds during fermentation, which are responsible for the flavors and aromas you find in passionfruit, mango, guava and other tropical fruits. Pair it up with hops that have high levels of thiols already (like Nelson Sauvin & Mosaic), and we’re in business! Laser phocused, in fact, on bringing you the juiciest hop flavors imaginable, and this is a first step in that direction! #TTB
...
And of course, credit to our very talented ASB Junior Cellarman, Phil Houston, for the cheeky portrayal of the one they call DAUV. May he rain in PDX! 🍻🤙🔊
